content.description: Sit start on the uphill side of the boulder on bad slopers with feet way underneath the boulder. Slap bad slopers to the left across the arete and join Blunt. Joining Blunt is the crux. Finish on Blunt.
content.location: On the uphill side of the hueco boulder.

content.description: Start as far back as you want in the small cave/roof and climb out close to the lip and trend out left a little. Climb out of the roof on really cool two and three finger pockets. Really good. Perfect for the grade.
content.protection: A couple pads and a spotter. Usually has a wet landing.
content.location: The Hueco Boulder. Farther up the shoreline to the north.

content.description: Start way back in the cave the same as for Skull Cap. Climb out the right side of the roof through some tricky layback moves.

Start the same as for Strong Jonhs Blunt but instead of finishing on Blunt keep traversing across the arete to the left eventually gaining good holds to the right of Skelletor. A tricky right hand cross move gets you around the arete.
content.location: On the Hueco Boulder. Starts on the uphill side and traverses closer  to the northern side of the boulder.

content.description: Climbs the blunt arete to the right and up above the hueco cave. Start with hands spanned across the arete and bump and slap your way up.

The large boulder farther north along the shore with a little more than 10 feet of horizontal roof climbing! There is nothing like this boulder in New England! No joke! The underside of the roof has been erroded by the tide and large hueco-like holds have resulted. Go check this boulder out!
